HEADWORD: Latus rectum
<hw>La"tus rec"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the
right side.]</ety> <fld>(Conic Sections)</fld> <def>The line drawn
through a focus of a conic section parallel to the directrix and
terminated both ways by the curve. It is the parameter of the principal
axis. See <er>Focus</er>, and <er>Parameter</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laud</ent>⟦br⟧
